title: Nana Kobina Osoh
text:
Nana Kobina Osoh (born 15 September 2001) is a Ghanaian professional footballer who plays as a midfielder for Ghanaian Premier League side <a href="Techiman%20Eleven%20Wonders%20FC">Techiman Eleven Wonders FC</a>. He is also a member of the <a href="Ghana%20national%20under-20%20football%20team">Ghana national under-20 football team</a>. He previously played for Maccabi Petah Tikva on loan.
Career.
Early career.
Osoh started his career with <a href="Division%20Two%20League%2C%20Ghana">Ghana Division Two League</a> side Golden Kick Sporting Club before moving to Israel on a season long loan deal.
Maccabi Petah Tikva (loan).
In September 2020, <a href="Maccabi%20Petah%20Tikva%20F.C.">Maccabi Petah Tikva</a> signed Osoh on a season long loan deal and assigned him to their U-19 side to booster their side in the <a href="UEFA%20Youth%20League">UEFA Youth League</a>. He played two matches for the U-19 side in the <a href="2019%E2%80%9320%20UEFA%20Youth%20League">2019–20 UEFA Youth League</a>.
Techiman Eleven Wonders (loan).
Osoh began his career in the Ghana Premier league with Bono-side <a href="Techiman%20Eleven%20Wonders%20FC">Techiman Eleven Wonders</a>, moving to the club on loan ahead of the <a href="2020%E2%80%9321%20Ghana%20Premier%20League">2020–21 Ghana Premier League</a>. He made his professional debut on 3 January 2021 in a 1–0 loss match against <a href="International%20Allies%20F.C.">International Allies</a>, coming on a substitute for <a href="Abu%20Musa%20Sule">Abu Musa Sule</a> in the 57th minute. He scored his first professional goal in a match against <a href="Karela%20United%20FC">Karela United</a>, scoring in the 79th minute after coming on in the 76th minute for <a href="McCarthy%20Ofori">McCarthy Ofori</a> to help Eleven Wonders win by 3–1.
